==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bidet
<hw>Bi*det"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>bidet</ets>, perh. fr. Celtic; cr. Gael. <ets>bideach</ets> very
little, diminutive, <ets>bidein</ets> a diminutive animal, W.
<ets>bidan</ets> a weakly or sorry wretch.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A small horse formerly allowed to each trooper or
dragoon for carrying his baggage.</def> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of bath tub for sitting baths; a sitz
bath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bidigitate</ent>⟦br⟧
